A MAN was taken to hospital after being hit by a van during the morning rush hour. Man struck by van in Glasgow's Gallowgate A MAN was taken to hospital after being hit by a van during the morning rush hour.The collision happened shortly after 9am on Thursday at the Gallowgate in the East End.The male pedestrian suffered a head injury in the crash and was taken by ambulance to Glasgow Royal Infirmary.A Police Scotland spokeswoman said: &quot;A man was struck by a van near the Bellgrove Hotel in Gallowgate at 9.05am.&quot;He was taken to hospital.&quot; 